  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support our school for the disabled in Nicaragua</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In 2009, the Nicaragua Children&apos;s Foundation started the first ever school for the disabled in the area of San Juan del Sur, Nicaragua. Until that time, children and adults with disabilities had no place to go during the day because  public schools were unable to accommodate them. This in turn meant that the parent who stayed home to care for them was unable to seek employment. The school, Los Pipitos, provides a place for children to learn and grow and allows their families a necessary respite.</narrative>
  </description>
